WE DONT NEED the IO (or the DCN or anything) to be the direct discrepancy between the wanted behavior and the actuall behavior, it is the fact that the DCN uniformize the IO activity and fail to do so IF there is a discrepancy that makes the IO bein as an emergent property the error between whiched and what is happening. AND it is the correction of the DCN code that indirectly put the DCN code at the right place to correct the behavior either right now for target alignement or in the exact same situation in the near futur for the gradient alignement. THis is the whole point of the model and the whole claim. We bypass the troublesome fact that we need to compute the discrepency elsewhere. You have to think deeply about that. the IO signal doesn't have to be be tied to a task-relevant residual from the outside, when trying to uniformize (not set to 0 if not bipolar units) the IO activity the DCN has to learn through backprop the right projection matrix. As the DCN has a default random code making some units activated at the same moment IO units are activated, backprop will learn to "increase the gain" on the right DCN neurons and these will learn to inhibit the right IO. This is the path of less resistance for backprop. another less plausible scenario will be for backprop to ignore the priming of certain units in the DCN due to there specific inputs and just generate the right signal only through PC DCN relay. Btw the whole model also works without DCN inputs when you have backprop, to uniformize the random specific activity of the IO backprop has as an only way to create a specific code in the DCN otherwise error will emerge as there is no trivial solution to uniformaize a random code which changes at any moment in time. So yes maybe the DCN inputs are not necessary when using backprop. but for the bio realistic version with only local plasticity it is certainly.  

